From 282c924281d029b4aa42676d98e3010e026329e5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Josh Law <objecting@objecting.org>
Date: Sun, 12 Apr 2026 19:44:46 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] lib/asn1_encoder: fix corrupted ASN.1 OID encoding for zero
 digits

The OID digit encoder contains a fast path for encoding the value 0. It incorrectly encodes this value as 0x80.

In standard ASN.1 BER/DER encoding, base-128 is used. The most significant bit (0x80) signals that more bytes follow for the current digit. Setting 0x80 for a standalone zero digit creates an invalid, non terminating byte sequence, which completely corrupts the OID and causes standard decoders to fail.

Change the fast-path encoding to 0x00 to produce a valid standard OID component.

Signed-off-by: Josh Law <objecting@objecting.org>
---
 lib/asn1_encoder.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/lib/asn1_encoder.c b/lib/asn1_encoder.c
index 92f35aae13b1..690ad43d37f4 100644
--- a/lib/asn1_encoder.c
+++ b/lib/asn1_encoder.c
@@ -97,7 +97,7 @@ static int asn1_encode_oid_digit(unsigned char **_data, int *data_len, u32 oid)
 
 	/* quick case */
 	if (oid == 0) {
-		*data++ = 0x80;
+		*data++ = 0x00;
 		(*data_len)--;
 		goto out;
 	}
-- 
